OL,3,CJulie Etchingham looks at how the
OL,4,Cgovernment are tackling violence
OL,5,Cagainst women
OL,7,FEvery week 2-3 women are killed by a
OL,8,Fcurrent or former partner, around 90
OL,9,Fwomen every year. These extreme acts
OL,10,Fof violence are usually perpetrated by
OL,11,Fmen, against women and in their own
OL,12,Fhomes.
OL,14,FYet, if a woman is stabbed to death in
OL,15,Fthe street by a stranger the starting
OL,16,Fsentencing point for murder is 25
OL,17,Fyears. If she is stabbed and killed in
OL,18,Fher own kitchen by her partner: it's
OL,19,Fjust 15.
