OL,3,CJulie Etchingham looks at how the
OL,4,Cgovernment are tackling violence
OL,5,Cagainst women
OL,7,FAs far as the families know, there had
OL,8,Fnever been a history of physical
OL,9,Fviolence prior to the attacks, but for
OL,10,FPoppy and Ellie, there was evidence of
OL,11,Fcontrolling and coercive behaviour.
OL,12,FCarole Gould said: " She told me that
OL,13,Fhe was becoming a bit controlling
OL,14,Fthose last couple of weeks and we
OL,15,Ftalked about it and I said to her, you
OL,16,Fdo not want to go out with somebody
OL,17,FEllie who sounds like he's become
OL,18,Fobsessed with you. But I could never
OL,19,Fhave imagined the danger she was in
OL,20,Fwhen I left to go to work that
OL,21,Fmorning."
