OL,3,CJulie Etchingham looks at how the
OL,4,Cgovernment are tackling violence
OL,5,Cagainst women
OL,7,FCarole, Julie and Elaine thought their
OL,8,Fsuffering couldn't get any worse after
OL,9,Ftheir daughters were murdered. But
OL,10,Fwhen they heard the sentences given to
OL,11,Fthe men who brutally killed them -
OL,12,Fthey were devastated.
OL,14,FEllie's killer Thomas Griffiths was a
OL,15,Ffew months from his 18th birthday and
OL,16,Fwas sentenced as a juvenile. He
OL,17,Freceived 12.5 years.
OL,19,FJoe Atkinson, was jailed for a minimum
OL,20,Fof 16 years for Poppy's murder.
