OL,3,CJulie Etchingham looks at how the
OL,4,Cgovernment are tackling violence
OL,5,Cagainst women
OL,7,FThe judge in Ross McCullum's trial
OL,8,Fsentenced him to serve a minimum of 23
OL,9,Fyears, citing cutting Megan's throat a
OL,10,Fvery substantial aggravating factor.
OL,12,FThese sentences hinge on the fact that
OL,13,Fknives already in the home were used
OL,14,Fto commit the murders - this carries a
OL,15,Fminimum tariff of 15 years.
OL,17,FHad the women been stabbed in the
OL,18,Fstreet with a knife taken to the
OL,19,Fscene, the starting point would be 25
OL,20,Fyears. It's a ten year disparity their
OL,21,Fmothers want to see changed.
