OL,3,CJulie Etchingham looks at how the
OL,4,Cgovernment are tackling violence
OL,5,Cagainst women
OL,7,FElaine, Julie and Carole feel the 10
OL,8,Fyear gap is insulting to their
OL,9,Fdaughters and for all victims of
OL,10,Fdomestic homicide, who are usually
OL,11,Fwomen.
OL,13,FCarole Gould, Ellie's mother, told
OL,14,FJulie: " We can't do anything to bring
OL,15,Four girls back. But if we can raise
OL,16,Fawareness and bring in longer
OL,17,Fsentences for these very dangerous
OL,18,Fmen, then we are guarding against
OL,19,Ffuture victims and we can't do
OL,20,Fanything more than that in our girls'
OL,21,Fnames."
