OL,3,CJulie Etchingham looks at how the
OL,4,Cgovernment are tackling violence
OL,5,Cagainst women
OL,7,FRecognising the growing concern over
OL,8,Fsentencing for domestic homicide - the
OL,9,Fgovernment commissioned Clare Wade KC
OL,10,Fto carry out an independent review. It
OL,11,Fwas published last year and Wade
OL,12,Fproposed a raft of measures - but
OL,13,Fcontroversially, did not recommend an
OL,14,Fincrease in the minimum tariff of 15
OL,15,Fyears.
OL,17,FThose who support that position point
OL,18,Fto the fact domestic violence and
OL,19,Fhomicide have complexities other
OL,20,Fcrimes may not.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G16/32
