OL,3,CJulie Etchingham looks at how the
OL,4,Cgovernment are tackling violence
OL,5,Cagainst women
OL,7,FHarriet Wistrich, Director at the
OL,8,FCentre for Women's Justice is
OL,9,Fconcerned: "if the minimum tariff was
OL,10,Fraised from 15 years to 25 years, then
OL,11,Fit would have the impact of indirect
OL,12,Fdiscrimination against women who kill
OL,13,Ftheir intimate partners. Because we
OL,14,Fknow that almost all women do so
OL,15,Fbecause they're a victim of his abuse.
OL,16,FIf they had managed to defend
OL,17,Fthemselves and survive, they shouldn't
OL,18,Fthen be sent to prison for 25 years
OL,19,Fplus for doing that."
