OL,3,CJulie Etchingham looks at how the
OL,4,Cgovernment are tackling violence
OL,5,Cagainst women
OL,7,FBut Hetti Barkworth-Nanton, Chair of
OL,8,FRefuge is in favour of an increase in
OL,9,Fthe minimum tariff, arguing the
OL,10,Fjustice system should simply adapt
OL,11,Fsentencing to protect, where
OL,12,Fnecessary, women who kill their
OL,13,Fabusers: "The number of women who kill
OL,14,Fin those circumstances are tiny
OL,15,Fcompared to the number of women who
OL,16,Fare being murdered every single day in
OL,17,Four homes. The answer to this problem
OL,18,Fis to get the courts to properly
OL,19,Funderstand and reflect the abuse that
OL,20,Fthey've been suffering, then women who
OL,21,Fare abused and who kill their
OL,22,Fperpetrator are simply excluded from
OL,23,Fthe 25 year regime."
